```bash
# Install Apache
sudo apt update
sudo apt install apache2 -y

# Start Apache
sudo systemctl start apache2
sudo systemctl enable apache2

# Install XCA (GUI Certificate Authority Tool)
sudo apt install xca -y

# Create a working directory
mkdir ~/pki-lab
cd ~/pki-lab

# Launch XCA
xca
```

### Inside XCA

#### Step 1: Create Database

```text
File → New Database
Filename: text.xdb
Choose a password
Save
```

---

#### Step 2: Create Root CA Private Key

```text
Private Keys → New Key
Name: RootCA-Key
Key Type: RSA
Key Size: 2048
Create
```

---

#### Step 3: Create Root CA Certificate

```text
Certificates → New Certificate

Source:
✓ Create a self signed certificate

Subject:
CN = RootCA
O = Example
C = IN

Extensions:
Basic Constraints:
✓ CA = TRUE

Key Usage:
✓ Certificate Sign
✓ CRL Sign

OK
```

Export:

```text
Certificates → RootCA → Export
Format: PEM (*.crt)
Save as: ca.crt
```

Export private key:

```text
Private Keys → RootCA-Key → Export
Format: PEM
Save as: root.pem
```

---

#### Step 4: Create Bob Private Key

```text
Private Keys → New Key

Name: Bob-Key
RSA
2048 bits
Create
```

Export:

```text
Private Keys → Bob-Key → Export
Format: PEM
Save as: bob.pem
```

---

#### Step 5: Create Bob Certificate

```text
Certificates → New Certificate

Template:
HTTPS_Server

Subject:
CN = bob.example.com
O = Example
C = IN

Signing:
Use Private Key: Bob-Key
Sign with: RootCA

Extensions:
CA = FALSE

OK
```

Export:

```text
Certificates → bob.example.com → Export

Format: PEM
Save as:
bob.example.com.crt
```

---

