```

---

### Configure Apache SSL

Create SSL directory:

```bash
sudo mkdir -p /etc/apache2/ssl
```

Copy certificates:

```bash
sudo cp bob.example.com.crt /etc/apache2/ssl/
sudo cp bob.pem /etc/apache2/ssl/
sudo cp ca.crt /etc/apache2/ssl/
```

Enable SSL:

```bash
sudo a2enmod ssl
sudo systemctl restart apache2
```

---

### Create Web Page

```bash
sudo mkdir -p /var/www/bob.example.com
```

```bash
sudo nano /var/www/bob.example.com/index.html
```

Paste:

```html
<html>
<head>
<title>Bob Secure Website</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>Welcome to Bob Secure Website</h1>
<h2>HTTPS Enabled using XCA Certificates</h2>
</body>
</html>
```

Save:

```text
Ctrl + O
Enter
Ctrl + X
```

---

### Create Virtual Host

```bash
sudo nano /etc/apache2/sites-available/bob.example.com.conf
```

Paste:

```apache
<VirtualHost *:443>

ServerName bob.example.com
DocumentRoot /var/www/bob.example.com

SSLEngine on

SSLCertificateFile /etc/apache2/ssl/bob.example.com.crt
SSLCertificateKeyFile /etc/apache2/ssl/bob.pem

<Directory /var/www/bob.example.com>
AllowOverride All
Require all granted
</Directory>

</VirtualHost>
```

Save and exit.

---

### Enable Site

```bash
sudo a2ensite bob.example.com.conf
```

Check config:

```bash
sudo apache2ctl configtest
```

Expected:

```text
Syntax OK
```

Restart Apache:

```bash
sudo systemctl restart apache2
```

---

### Add Host Entry

```bash
sudo nano /etc/hosts
```

Add:

```text
127.0.0.1    bob.example.com
```

Save.

---

### Verify

Open browser:

```text
https://bob.example.com
```

Or test from terminal:

```bash
curl -k https://bob.example.com
```

Check certificate:

```bash
openssl x509 -in bob.example.com.crt -text -noout
```

Check Apache SSL:

```bash
openssl s_client -connect bob.example.com:443
```

Final files:

```text
text.xdb
root.pem
ca.crt
bob.pem
bob.example.com.crt
/var/www/bob.example.com/index.html
/etc/apache2/sites-available/bob.example.com.conf
```
